I wanted to fly since I was very little.
And I did it today… today, I flew an airplane. I still can't believe it.
flightaware data.
I'm going to try to go again on Saturday. The weather isn't great right now, but it's only Monday.
The difficulties are already starting to appear. I will probably have A LOT of trouble getting a medical certificate, due to the FAA's stance on certain medications.
Not impossible, but it will take ENORMOUSLY much time and require A LOT more work.
Even though it's discouraging, it's just another problem to solve, and for now, it seems *completely* manageable to me. It's just that it will take a lot of time and $$.
In case the challenge I face interests you.
The FAA isn't a fan of ADHD. It doesn't issue a medical certificate if you're undergoing treatment for it.
